Gabriel Jesus scored four times as Manchester City kept the Premier League title race in their own hands by thrashing Watford 5-1 at the Etihad Stadium. Jesus netted twice within 23 minutes, with Rodri drilling home a stunning third after Hassane Kamara pulled one back for the Hornets midway through an entertaining first half.   Fury beats Whyte to retain world boxing heavyweight title     Tottenham held by Brentford to dent top-four hopes     Arsenal beat Man United to boost top-four hopes   The Brazilian celebrated twice more within eight minutes of the restart as relegation-threatened Watford collapsed, Jesus first winning and converting a penalty before sweeping home from Kevin De Bruyne’s pass. All eyes will now turn to Anfield on Sunday, where title challengers Liverpool will attempt to keep pace with Pep Guardiola’s men by beating rivals, Everton. Jesus needed just four minutes to give City the lead, turning home Oleksandr Zinchenko’s fierce left-wing cross after the Ukrainian latched onto Joao Cancelo’s overhit ball.